TASK 2 – INSIDE A COMPUTER SYSTEM

Motherboard
• Sabhi hardware components ko connect karti hai.
• Data communication ka main pathway.

Human Analogy: Skeleton

CPU (Central Processing Unit)
• Computer ka Brain.
• Instructions execute karta hai.
• Processing aur calculations karta hai.

Human Analogy: Brain

RAM (Random Access Memory)
• Temporary (Volatile) memory.
• Running programs ka data store karti hai.
• Power off hone par data delete ho jata hai.

Human Analogy: Short-Term Memory

Storage (SSD / HDD)
• Permanent (Non-Volatile) storage.
• Operating System, files aur software permanently store hote hain.

Human Analogy: Long-Term Memory

PSU (Power Supply Unit)
• Computer ko power supply deta hai.
• AC ko DC me convert karta hai.

Human Analogy: Heart

GPU (Graphics Processing Unit)
• Graphics aur videos process karta hai.
• Gaming, Editing aur AI workloads me use hota hai.

Human Analogy: Eyes

Cooling System
• CPU aur GPU ko overheat hone se bachata hai.

Human Analogy: Body Cooling System

