TASK 3 – WHAT HAPPENS WHEN YOU PRESS THE START BUTTON?

Boot Sequence

1. Power Button
2. PSU supplies power
3. UEFI / BIOS starts
4. POST (Power-On Self Test)
5. Boot Device Selection
6. Bootloader starts
7. Operating System loads into RAM

Remember

Power
↓
UEFI / BIOS
↓
POST
↓
Boot Device
↓
Bootloader
↓
Operating System

Important Points

• UEFI BIOS ka modern version hai.
• POST hardware ko check karta hai.
• Bootloader Operating System ko RAM me load karta hai.
• OS load hone ke baad computer use ke liye ready ho jata hai.

